Approach No 1:

Submit Spark Job in EMR cluster:  (https://blog.sqreen.io/amazon-emr-spark/)

1) First we need to create Cluster on EMR(Graphically we can create)
2) When we will create out cluster, there we need to create EMR role & EC2 instance profile. The role may not be selected by default 
& we may need to create it using below command using awscli tool using below command:

aws emr create-cluster \
--name "My cluster" \
--instance-type m3.xlarge \
--release-label emr-5.4.0 \
--instance-count 3\
--use-default-roles \
--applications Name=Spark

3) Submitting jobs to the cluster via GUI. (https://blog.sqreen.io/amazon-emr-spark/)

4) Above result we can acheive using awscli :

[
 {
   "Name": "Spark application - test - 2",
   "Type":"CUSTOM_JAR",
   "Jar":"command-runner.jar",
   "Args":
   [
     "spark-submit",
     "--deploy-mode", "cluster",
     "s3://sqreen-spark/spark.py",
     "s3://sqreen-spark/input.json",
     "s3://sqreen-spark/output-files"
   ]
 }
]


5) Now,In the same directory,we can now run:

aws emr add-steps --cluster-id --steps file://step.json


6) Approach NO2: (http://queirozf.com/entries/creating-a-spark-cluster-on-aws-emr-a-tutorial)

7) Approach No3: To connect to the AWS Master Node node using PuTTY (https://docs.aws.amazon.com/emr/latest/ManagementGuide/emr-connect-master-node-ssh.html)

8) In place of IP address & hostname >>>use hadoop@ec2-###-##-##-###.compute-1.amazonaws.com (MasterPublicDNS from EMR instance)

Example viewing Cluster Status:

aws emr describe-cluster --cluster-id j-1K48XXXXXXHCB (--cluster-id from the EMR cluster)

9) Managing Spark Clusters on EMR using AWS CLI & SSH. (http://queirozf.com/entries/using-command-line-tools-to-manage-spark-clusters-on-emr-examples-and-reference)

10) https://www.slideshare.net/AmazonWebServices/aws-summit-tel-aviv-data-science-best-practices-for-apache-spark-on-amazon-emr (Number of ways

to submit Spark Job in AWS EMR cluster)

11) https://www.slideshare.net/AmazonWebServices/aws-summit-tel-aviv-data-science-best-practices-for-apache-spark-on-amazon-emr (Using other 
storage layers to submit saprk jobs)


12) https://docs.aws.amazon.com/emr/latest/ManagementGuide/emr-connect-master-node-ssh.html 
(Connect to the Master Node Using SSH and an Amazon EC2 Private Key on Linux, Unix, and Mac OS X)



